    en: "A driver on I-390 near Rochester hit a large pothole in the right travel lane, damaging the vehicle's suspension and alignment. The pothole had been reported to NYSDOT three weeks earlier by several other drivers through the 511 system. Within 60 days of the incident, the driver filed a Notice of Intention to File Claim in the Court of Claims, Western District, naming the State of New York. The Notice preserved the driver's right to file a formal claim within 2 years. Counsel gathered 511 reports, maintenance records, and a NYSDOT incident log through FOIL request showing prior written notice. A formal claim was filed 14 months later alleging highway maintenance negligence with prior notice to NYSDOT. The Attorney General's office answered denying liability. After discovery and a bench trial, the court found the State liable for $8,400 in vehicle damages and awarded that amount. No jury. No punitive damages. Appeal was not pursued."
